From 5ab031c6ba585ddda5e0a05d25ed669259898960 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Barry Jackson <barjac@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sat, 6 Jun 2026 17:57:52 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 3/7] Restore heard station list on launch (#1358)

* Restore heard callsign list from CSV log on startup and modem start.

On startup and each time the modem is started, read up to the 100 most
recent entries from the CSV RX log and pre-populate the stations-heard
list. Restored entries are shown in grey to distinguish them from
callsigns heard in the current session.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

* Enable Log QSO button based on list content, not modem state.

The log button is now live whenever the stations-heard list has entries,
allowing QSOs to be logged from the restored CSV list without needing to
start the modem.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

* Guard against null logger in log entry dialog.

logContact() was called unconditionally on a pointer that is null when
the modem is stopped or WSJT-X logging is not configured, causing a
segfault. Skip the WSJT-X forward when no logger is active.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

* Create temporary logger in log dialog when modem is stopped.

When the modem is not running the app-level logger is null. If UDP
reporting is configured, spin up a short-lived WSJTXNetworkLogger for
the single logContact() call so logging reaches the logging program
regardless of modem state.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

* Add PR #1358 to changelog.

---------

Co-authored-by: Barry Jackson <barjac@mageia.org>
Co-authored-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Co-authored-by: Mooneer Salem <mooneer@gmail.com>
