From 052c4d79feca2d516f774b18d5e683f1c8b26d38 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Barry Jackson <barjac@mageia.org>
Date: Sun, 7 Jun 2026 18:14:33 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 4/7] Redesign BeepStep to eliminate pipeline switches at
 start/end of TOT beep.
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

BeepStep is now always present in the pipeline and acts as a pure passthrough
when idle — polling g_totBeepActive each buffer. This removes the EitherOrStep
that was switching the pipeline on/off for the beep, which caused PipeWire to
re-initialize its audio stream (producing ~500ms noise bursts at both ends of
the notification).

Also removes g_totBeepActive from the eitherOrRfDemodulationStep condition so
the RF demodulator runs continuously throughout the beep without causing a
separate upstream pipeline switch.

