From 4557a1e9f649973edffed26cf29a39b40027d8ff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Barry Jackson <barjac@mageia.org>
Date: Sun, 7 Jun 2026 21:38:12 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 5/7] Fix TOT beep pipeline stall during TX-stop sequence.

stopTotBeep_() clears g_totBeepActive before g_tx becomes false, causing
rxProcessing_ to evaluate processInputFifo=false (half-duplex TX, no monitor,
no beep flag) and call clearFifos_(), stalling the pipeline mid-beep.  The
stall inserts silence into the speaker output; the abrupt resume mid-tone
produces clicks and can make Morse '5' sound like S+I.

Add s_totBeepPlaying (set when BeepStep activates, cleared on completion) and
include it in processInputFifo so the pipeline keeps running throughout the
full beep regardless of when g_totBeepActive is externally cleared.

Also fix BeepStep::reset() to clear playing_ so the step is safe to reset
from external code paths.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
